<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-BVYiiSIFeK1dGmJRAkycuHAHRg32OmUcww7on3RYdg4Va+PmSTsz/K68vbdEjh4u"
    crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/main.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Amatic+SC:400,700|Open+Sans+Condensed:300,700|Open+Sans:400,700,800" rel="stylesheet">  </head>

    <div id='page2'>
      <body>
        <header>
          <div class='heading1'>
            <h1>Just The Tip...</h1>`
          </div>

          <div class="heading2">
            <h2>A place to talk/learn about everything sex.</h2>
          </div>
        </header>

        <ul class="nav nav-tabs">
          <li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="/">Home</a></li>
          <li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="/posts/new">Create New Post</a></li>
        </ul>

          <section class="tag-types">
            <p>This forum can be used to not only ask questions and learn a thing or two, but to share stories
               of the successful and the not so successful. Gloat a little. It's ok, just as long as good thorough instructions follow!
               Have an experience that just went south real fast? Let us know so we don't go down the same road. In order to give readers
               a head's up on your topic, include one of these tags in your post. Just copy and paste into the tag line so we can organize where
               your story will live.</p><br/>
          </section>

          <h3>Topic Tag</h3>

          <div class='topic-nav'>
            <nav class="topic">
              <ul class='topic'>
                <li class="topic">I have a question...</li>
                <li class="topic">Things that worked!</li>
                <li class="topic">Things that didn't</li>
                <li class="topic">You want me to put what where?!</li>
              </ul>
            </nav>
          </div>


            <h3>Previous posts</h3>
              <ul class='topic-loop'>
                <% for (let i = 0; i < posts.length; i++) { %>
                <li class='topic-loop'>
                    <a class='topic-loop' href="/posts/<%=posts[i]._id%>"> <%=posts[i].tag%></a>
                </li>
                <% } %>
              </ul>
      </body>
    </div>
</html>
